date=18 March 2012}}</ref> In July it was announced that Khali was undergoing surgery for a benign tumor found in his pituitary gland due to [[acromegaly]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/WWE_News_3/article_63784.shtml|title=PWTorch.com - WWE News: ABC News report - What led to Great Khali's tumor surgery, can he wrestle again?, WWE at fault?|website=www.pwtorch.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=WWE Star Great Khali's Growth-Inducing Tumor Removed|date=29 July 2012|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/star-wrestler-great-khali-tumor-removed-caused-size/story?id=16874060#.UBXAEd_iUtn|work=ABC News|author=Harish, Alon}}</ref> Khali returned at the ''SmackDown'' tapings on 16 October in a match taped for ''[[WWE Saturday Morning Slam|Saturday Morning Slam]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/artman/publish/WWE/article10027883.shtml|title=WWE News: Wrestler returns to the ring following a medical leave|website=prowrestling.net}}</ref>

