 2013}}</ref>

At [[WrestleMania XXX]] on 6 April, Khali competed in the [[André the Giant Memorial Battle Royal]], but failed to win.<ref>{{cite web|last=Meltzer|first=Dave|title=WWE Wrestlemania 30 live coverage & results: The Streak is over, Daniel Bryan's reign begins|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe/36326-wrestlemania-live-coverage-from-the-superdome-in-new-orleans|work=[[Wrestling Observer]]|accessdate=10 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701230803/http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe/36326-wrestlemania-live-coverage-from-the-superdome-in-new-orleans|archivedate=1 July 2015}}</ref> Khali participated in the [[WWE Intercontinental Championship|Intercontinental Championship]] battle royal at [[Battleground (2014)|Battleground]] on 20 July, but the match was won by The Miz.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/PPVReports/2014/07/21/21820686.html|title=Cena, Usos survive Battleground|date=21 July 2014|last=Powell|first=John|accessdate=20 April 2016|work=Slam! Sports|publisher=[[Canadian Online Explorer]]}}</ref> On 31 October episode of ''SmackDown'', Khali was defeated by [[Rusev (wrestler)|Rusev]] in what would be his final match in WWE until 2017, as on 13 November his contract expired and he left WWE.<ref>[http://www.pwinsider.com/article/89572/great-khali-update.html?p=1 "GREAT KHALI UPDATE | PWInsider.com"]. ''pwinsider.com''.</ref>

